THE KRAIT PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE TL;DR

* KraitDev owns the official Krait Programming Language project.

* Anyone can use, modify, and share the code for free (open source).

* If you "fork" (copy) the compiler itself to make your own version, 
  you CANNOT claim you invented it, and you MUST change the name so it 
  does not use "Krait Programming Language" or the official logo.

* You CAN use the "Krait Programming Language" name and official logo 
  to build, brand, and promote tools, packages, or libraries created 
  for the Krait ecosystem, as long as it is clear your tool is an 
  independent community creation.

* The word "krait" can be used completely freely by anyone for 
  anything else outside of programming languages (like for games, 
  snakes, clothes, or stories).
